description:
The New York State Department of Financial Services seeks to build an equitable, transparent, and resilient financial system that benefits individuals and supports business. Through engagement, data-driven regulation and policy, and operational excellence, the Department and its employees are responsible for empowering consumers and protecting them from financial harm; ensuring the health of the entities we regulate; driving economic growth in New York through responsible innovation; and preserving the stability of the global financial system.

The Department of Financial Services is seeking candidates for the position of Director of Market Regulation in the Property Bureau. The incumbent will oversee approximately half of all the staff in the Property Bureau, including core underwriting and market conduct functions. Duties include, but are not limited to, the following:

· Reviews and processes all form and rate filings (except Private Passenger general rate filings) which relate to automobile insurance coverages and consumer complaints relative thereto;

· Supervises all first party property insurance products including homeowners and commercial multi-peril policies and consumer complaints relative thereto;

· Reviews and processes of all rate and form filings which relate to liability coverages, and consumer complaints relative thereto;

· Coordinates all Bureau activities in the area of legislation, regulation, circular letters, NAIC activities and research;

· Conducts field investigations to determine insurer compliance with the Insurance Law, Regulations and Circular Letters and conformity with filed forms, rates. rating rules, rating plans, etc., fair claim practice regulations and automobile no-fault regulations, verification of data submitted with rate filings, Department of Motor Vehicles Financial Security Program, New York Automobile Insurance Plan performance standards; and conducts statutory examinations of NYPIUA, ELANY and NY licensed rate service organizations;

· Analyzes the underlying costs of automobile and no-fault insurance, including vehicle repair costs and medical services utilization; and administers the auto physical damage inspection regulation (Regulation 79);

· Oversees the overall administration of the New York No-Fault Laws;

· Supervises the excess and surplus lines insurance market including ELANY, and registrations of risk retention groups and purchasing groups organized pursuant to the Federal Risk Retention Act;

· Conducts investigations of excess line brokers and recommends fines and consent order settlements of brokers in violation of the excess line statutes and regulations;

· Analyzes all statistical data received by the Bureau;

· Prepares all statutorily mandated reports; and

· Other job duties as assigned.

**Preferred Qualifications**

· A bachelor’s degree, law degree, and at least 9 years of relevant work experience including 5 years in the insurance or financial services industry;

· At least 4 years of managerial supervision with a demonstrated ability to supervise large teams;

· General familiarity with insurance regulation and New York Insurance Law;

· Superior written and oral communication skills and strong analytical skills;

· Strong intellectual, analytical and management skills.

**Appointment method:**

This is an appointment to a position in the exempt jurisdictional class. As such, the incumbent of this position would serve at the pleasure of the appointing authority.

To Apply: Interested qualified candidates must submit a resume and letter of interest to the email address listed below. Please include Box# (Box DMR**- DFDP3-10131) in the subject line of your email to ensure receipt of your application. Email submissions are preferred.**

